Common Issues & Solutions

NotSupportedError

WebAuthn not supported. Try Chrome/Safari on a device with biometric sensors (iPhone with Face ID/Touch ID, Mac with Touch ID, Windows with Windows Hello).

NotAllowedError

User cancelled or timeout. Make sure to complete the biometric prompt when it appears. Check if biometric authentication is enabled in device settings.

SecurityError

Security requirements not met. Ensure you're using HTTPS (or localhost for development) and the domain is properly configured.

InvalidStateError

Authenticator already registered. Try authentication instead, or clear existing credentials and register again.

No Platform Authenticator

Device doesn't have a built-in biometric sensor or it's disabled. Check device settings for Face ID, Touch ID, Windows Hello, etc.
